= class GLib::UnixOutputStream

== Object Hierarchy

* Object
  * GLib::Instantiatable
    * GLib::Object
      * GLib::OutputStream
        * GLib::UnixOutputStream

== Class Methods

--- GLib::UnixOutputStream.new

     * Returns: self: ((*FIXME*))

== Instance Methods

--- close_fd=(close_fd)

    Sets the value whether to close the file descriptor when the stream is closed or not.
     * close_fd: true if to close the file descriptor when the stream is closed
     * Returns: close_fd

--- close_fd?

    Gets the value whether to close the file descriptor when the stream is closed or not.
     * Returns: true if to close the file descriptor when the stream is closed

--- fd

    Gets the file descriptor to write to.
     * Returns: The file descriptor to write to

--- set_close_fd(close_fd)

    Same as close_fd=.
     * close_fd: true if to close the file descriptor when the stream is closed
     * Returns: self

== Properties

--- close-fd: true or false (Read/Write)

    Whether to close the file descriptor when the stream is closed

--- fd: Integer (Read/Write)

    The file descriptor to write to

